narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A very good introduction to basic processing that doesn't get a whole lot of attention in the psychology department. Professor Marks a very good teacher to have--he knows a ton of information--and you really come out feeling like you've learned something. Highly recommended.

It is genuinely a really great class if you're interested in the subject matter at all. The professor is really smart and has had a hand in all the most meaningful research in physiology and psychology to date.
